after downloading the iso you will need to prepare a bootable media, dvd or usb drive 

for Microsoft Windows users head to pendrive linux http://www.pendrivelinux.com/  download  and install Universal USB Installer 

a usb removable drive with a minimum of 4gb is needed for this iso

follow the instruction to pick the correct drive and micrometre.iso

after preparing the boot media

restart your computer and enter the boot menu by reapply pressing del , f12,f8
the above depends on the manufacturers most use f12 or del 

keep heating those buttons and you will be presented with a menu 

look for usb removable media and hit enter

you will be presented with the boot menu for micrometre OS 

choose the default option recommended

